Helvidius Priscus is fully described in H. iv 5. He was quaestor

of Achaia under Nero (Schol. on Juv. v 36), and shortly afterwards married Thrasea’s daughter Fannia. After returning from the exile to which he was condemned by Nero, he was prominent in attacking Eprius Marcellus, and became praetor in 70 Α. D.
